B6 - Attend 2 cyber ethics/law related talks/seminars

Objective
The goal of this activity was to understand the ethical and legal aspects of cybersecurity through attending seminars focused on cyber laws and responsible technology use.

Method
I attended two online seminars related to cybersecurity ethics and laws through video presentations. The sessions focused on data privacy, legal responisibilities, and ethical issues in cybersecurity.

Seminar 1 - Key points learned
- Importance of dat privacy and protection
- Organisations must handle user data responsibly
- Legal consequences of data breaches
- Users have right over their personal data

Seminar 2 - Key points learned
- Ethical responisbilities in cybersecurity
- Difference between ethical hacking and illegal hacking
- Importance of following laws and regulations
- Consequences of cybercrime activities

Outcome
These seminars helped me understand the legal and ethical responsiblities onvolved in cybersecurity, both for individuals and organisations.

Reflection
This activity highlighted that cybersecurity is not only technical but also involves ethical decision-making and legal comliance. It reinforced the importance of using cybersecurity knowledge responsibly and understanding the consequences of misuse.
